1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Be7 6. Bd3 {A robust approach
that should not be underestimated.} (6. Be3 {A somewhat clumsy natural
development for White.} O-O 7. Qd2 (7. f3 d5 $1 {A successful central blow.} 8.
exd5 (8. e5 {Agsinst the advance of the white central pawn I recommend} Ne8 $1
$146 9. Nb3 c6 10. Bd3 f6 11. exf6 Nxf6 {With a good game for Black.}) 8... Bb4
$5 {This pin is the most ambitious attempt for Black.} ({It is also possible
to play the healthy} 8... Nxd5 $11) 9. Bc4 (9. Bg5 h6 10. Bxf6 (10. Bh4 g5 11.
Bf2 Nxd5 $36) 10... Qxf6 11. Qd3 Re8+ 12. Nde2 Qg5 $44 {Black has compensation
for the pawn due to his superiority on the dark squares and his more active
pieces.} (12... Bf5 $5)) 9... Nxd5 10. Bxd5 Bxc3+ 11. bxc3 Qxd5 $15) (7. Be2 {
transposes to 6. Be2.}) 7... c6 8. O-O-O b5 9. f3 b4 10. Na4 $1 (10. Nb1 $6 {
This withdrawal is much more passive and a worse choice.} c5 11. Nb5 (11. Ne2
$6 Nc6 $17) 11... Qa5 12. Nxd6 Be6 {[%csl Ra2][%cal Ga5a2]} 13. e5 (13. a3 Nc6
14. Nc4 Qa6 $1 15. Nd6 (15. b3 Rad8 $15) 15... c4 $5 16. axb4 Rab8 17. b5 Rxb5
18. Nxb5 Qxb5 $40 {Black has an attack for the sacrificed exchange.}) 13...
Nfd7 14. a3 Nxe5 $15) 10... Qa5 (10... Bd7 $6 {has been played:} 11. b3 a6 12.
Nf5 {1-0 Xiong,J (2709)-Abdusattorov,N (2627) chess.com INT 2020} (12. g4 $16))
11. b3 c5 12. Nb5 Rd8 {[%cal Gb8c6,Gc8e6] Black's idea is simple: Nc6 / Be6,
and start an attack against the king. The first player must play very
carefully.} 13. Na3 $1 Be6 14. Nc4 Bxc4 15. Bxc4 Nbd7 {[%cal Gd7b6] Followed
by Nb6. Black has the initiative.}) 6... O-O 7. O-O Re8 8. h3 (8. Re1 Nbd7 {
White has different possibilities:} 9. h3 (9. b3 Nc5 10. Bb2 c6 11. Qf3 Nxd3
12. Qxd3 Bf8 13. Rad1 Qa5 ({Worth considering is} 13... Bg4 $5 {, with the
idea of provoking White to play f3.}) 14. h3 {After the solid} Bd7 {[%cal
Ga8d8] , the position is approximately balanced.} (14... Qh5 $6 15. Nde2 Qh4
$16 {1-0 (29) Naroditsky,D (2619)-Pakleza,Z (2496) chess.com INT 2018})) (9.
Nf5 Bf8 10. Bg5 h6 11. Bh4 Ne5 (11... c6 $5) 12. Ne3 c6 13. a4 a5 14. Rb1 Be7 {
, with equality.} (14... Ng6 $5)) 9... Bf8 10. Bg5 h6 11. Bh4 g6 (11... c6 {
Seems more flexible to me, and temporarily keeps the g6-square open for the
d7-knight (Ne5-g6).}) 12. Qf3 c6 13. Rad1 Bg7 $14 {0-1 (67) Villalba,M (2258)
-Praggnanandhaa,R (2608) chess.com INT 2020}) ({The direct} 8. Bg5 {did not
cause any inconveniences after} c6 9. Qd2 Qb6 10. Nb3 Nbd7 11. Kh1 a5 12. a4
Ne5 13. f4 Nxd3 14. Qxd3 h6 $11 {0-1 (33) Okara,A (2314)-Kabanov,N (2521)
Salekhard 2006}) (8. b3 c6 9. Bb2 Bf8 10. a4 Nbd7 11. Re1 Nc5 12. h3 a5 13. Qd2
Qb6 14. Rad1 Bd7 {Black is displaying his standard setup.} 15. Qf4 {Instead of
the usual 16...Rad8, Black has the more energetic} d5 $1 (15... Nxd3 16. Rxd3
