1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 e5 4. Nf3 exd4 5. Nxd4 Be7 6. Bf4 O-O 7. Qd2 d5 $5 {
This second option is the sharpest variation and involves material sacrifices
on the part of Black. It doesn't currently have the best reputation, and
analysis often gives White an advantage. However, it is very interesting to
have it in one's repertoire for two reasons. One: The positions are rich in
possibilities and offer room for potential improvement. And two: There is an
enormous number of complex variations that White must play perfectly. When
faced with a surprise, it is difficult to react in the best way over the board.
I present the main variations below and invite the reader to investigate this
very dangerous system.} 8. Ndb5 $1 {Entering into the complications. It is the
only move that offers problems to Black.} ({Other possibilities are:} 8. exd5
Nxd5 9. Nxd5 Qxd5 10. Nb5 Re8 $1 11. Be2 (11. Qxd5 $4 Bb4+ 12. Kd1 Re1#) 11...
Bb4 $1 12. Qxb4 Nc6 13. Qc3 Qxb5 14. Be3 Qb4 15. O-O Qxc3 16. bxc3 Na5 17. Rfd1
