1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 Be7 6. g3 O-O 7. Bg2 Re8 {
With this natural development, Black reaches positions typical of the Hanham
variation. As is typical in the Philidor defence, they offer a space advantage
for White while maintaining chances for a counterattack. The positions contain
a lot of central tension, with Black waiting for an opportunity to play a
liberating break. There are many moves for both sides that end up transposing.
I recommend concentrating on typical themes and manoeuvres.} 8. O-O Bf8 9. h3 (
{Another option is} 9. Re1 Nbd7 10. a4 c6 11. h3 a5 12. g4 g6 13. g5 Nh5 $13 {
0-1 (42) Nitin,S (2365) -Salgado Lopez,I (2626) Chennai 2011}) (9. Bf4 {
transposes to Chapter XV.}) (9. b3 {A calmer setup that seeks long-term
positional pressure.} Nbd7 10. Bb2 (10. Re1 c6 11. Bb2 Nc5 (11... Qb6 $2 12.
